One day, a Catholic offers to hire him to film a baptism and he refuses, on the basis that unlike birthday parties, baptisms directly support the Catholic faith and he can not provide such direct support to a ceremony based on a faith that he opposes.<br />
Is this a violation of the New Mexicoâs Human Rights Actâs prohibition against religious discrimination?<br />
Answer correctly, and you will know why and how the RFRA would apply.</p>

